cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and deep learning techniques for extracting drug-related information from hospital discharge summaries. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The use of pre-trained language models and semantic features also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) in the context of extracting drug-related information, which makes cs.IR a likely category. Finally, the use of recurrent neural networks suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category.
